all these people are the same.

00:00:45.079 --> 00:00:49.671
They are just trying to find
out how to condition people.

00:00:52.983 --> 00:00:58.402
I mean, if they give all their business and just
take to God, they will be so very much happier.

00:00:58.442 --> 00:01:00.942
And all this effort will be lost.

00:01:03.472 --> 00:01:09.708
Very serious things. You see, for
Christian community especially I think,

00:01:09.708 --> 00:01:16.061
it is that because of these
barriers, they may never reach God.

00:01:16.088 --> 00:01:22.597
It’s all right for Christians in the West because
they have seen the nonsense of it, most of them.

00:01:22.597 --> 00:01:27.968
But in the countries like ours,
you see which are developing,

00:01:27.982 --> 00:01:31.442
for them Christianity being
so sophisticated, so good,

00:01:31.442 --> 00:01:33.942
you see to them, Christians mean something great.

00:01:37.352 --> 00:01:47.373
My husband was telling Me that his own uncle wanted to become a Christian because he found that Hindu religion was so absurd,

00:01:47.407 --> 00:01:49.383
and the priests were so absurd.

00:01:49.383 --> 00:01:52.133
So he was so enamoured by Christians.

00:01:54.041 --> 00:01:56.541
I tell you.

00:02:01.641 --> 00:02:03.441
I suppose our biggest
problem is the Christians.

00:02:03.441 --> 00:02:07.994
We really don’t have any other barrier here.

00:02:08.014 --> 00:02:13.355
We have quite a few Muslims.
They can be a bit fanatical too.

00:02:14.395 --> 00:02:18.154
And the conversion, you see.
Conversion is another problem.

00:02:18.173 --> 00:02:27.133
Conversion in India is more in the places
where there are jungles and things

00:02:27.156 --> 00:02:29.656
where the people are
absolutely away from society.

00:02:29.656 --> 00:02:32.013
So for them, money is very important,

00:02:32.016 --> 00:02:39.443
and the way these people take the missionaries and their
food and this and that, so they are converting you.

00:02:39.443 --> 00:02:41.713
I mean donkeys after donkeys.

00:02:41.713 --> 00:02:44.213
But they have created
problems for us in the way,

00:02:44.213 --> 00:02:56.959
that these people say who are living in Khasia, Jaintia, all
these places you see – a former Nagaland sort of a thing.

00:02:56.959 --> 00:03:00.317
And this Nagaland business
is all a Christian problem.

00:03:00.336 --> 00:03:04.417
They have all become Christians you
see and don’t understand anything.

00:03:04.426 --> 00:03:10.237
At the time of Christ, I don’t
know if He ever went to this;

00:03:10.246 --> 00:03:12.761
it’s such primitive people.

00:03:12.796 --> 00:03:17.621
But Christianity has gone to them. They
don’t understand anything – A to Z.

00:03:17.630 --> 00:03:22.611
Now they came to Lal Bahadur
Shastri, our Prime Minister

00:03:22.649 --> 00:03:26.382
and they said that, “We
must have our sovereignty.”

00:03:26.378 --> 00:03:30.302
That’s what they said. They had written
it down in their language, ‘sovereignty’.

00:03:30.322 --> 00:03:32.299
So Shastriji asked, “What is sovereignty?”

00:03:32.314 --> 00:03:36.219
“That we don’t know. We
want our sovereignty.”

00:03:37.926 --> 00:03:40.426
“Then, what is sovereignty you want?”

00:03:40.426 --> 00:03:44.888
Then they said, “This is what
we have. We know one thing.”

00:03:44.922 --> 00:03:50.368
Then they said, “But what is it? That we
don’t know.”  “But why do you want it?”

00:03:50.368 --> 00:03:54.328
“That we don’t know.  We
want our sovereignty.”

00:03:55.810 --> 00:03:59.820
To the Prime Minister! The Prime Minister
said, “Oh God, these Christians.”

00:03:59.820 --> 00:04:06.710
And they were wearing suits and hats, funny hats
and suits and all Western dresses, you see.

00:04:06.710 --> 00:04:10.727
And they are all Christians in
Nagaland. And all stupid people.

00:04:11.342 --> 00:04:18.047
This is what they had got it, you see on a
paper. “We want our sovereignty.”  Finished.

00:04:18.628 --> 00:04:21.128
He could have given them anything.

00:04:22.438 --> 00:04:29.104
I was thinking, he should have given them some sort of an
odd paper and said, “This is sovereignty, you take it back.”

00:04:29.104 --> 00:04:31.415
They would have taken it.

00:04:32.382 --> 00:04:38.645
Such things they have got. And it’s created a
problem; this Nagaland is a problem for India now.

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:41.565
It’s the missionaries who have created.

00:04:41.565 --> 00:04:42.880
Yes, the missionaries.

00:04:42.880 --> 00:04:47.850
(in Marathi) They wrote it down in their language, “You
go and meet Shastriji and when you go there tell him,

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:50.350
we want our sovereignty, finished.”

00:04:50.350 --> 00:04:52.850
But Shastriji was non-plussed. He said,

00:04:52.850 --> 00:04:55.350
(in Marathi) “Then what next?”

00:04:55.350 --> 00:04:59.230
And in English, you see,
"We want our sovereignty.”

00:04:59.247 --> 00:05:02.920
(in Marathi) “Why do you want
it, sir?” “That we do not know.

00:05:02.954 --> 00:05:05.454
We want our sovereignty.”

00:05:06.914 --> 00:05:10.514
I tell you. When Shashtriji told
us, I didn’t know where to look.

00:05:10.514 --> 00:05:15.503
He said, “But this is too much. Just written
down that word in English, I mean this sentence

00:05:15.503 --> 00:05:20.678
and they were reading it out to me all the time. They would
not say what is sovereignty, why sovereignty – nothing.”

00:05:20.659 --> 00:05:23.949
Now missionaries, these then educated.

00:05:23.949 --> 00:05:29.369
Now the idea of missionaries – because
Church is always confused with...

00:05:29.389 --> 00:05:36.349
I mean the ruling people, like the kings and queens and also politics –

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:38.643
so now they are confused with that.

00:05:38.643 --> 00:05:41.990
So they want to create
a Christian land there.

00:05:42.033 --> 00:05:46.240
As it is, we have one Hindu
land, one Muslim land.

00:05:46.264 --> 00:05:51.788
Then we have one Sikh land. Then we’ll have one
Christian land. And there’s one Bangla land.

00:05:51.819 --> 00:05:56.544
So I don’t know how many parts of that country there
are going to be, of according to the religion.

00:05:56.556 --> 00:06:00.196
And nobody follows it, that’s the best part of it.

00:06:02.387 --> 00:06:06.636
And if you see, I saw the other day when
our Prime Minister went to Nagaland,

00:06:06.645 --> 00:06:10.027
they made him wear a hat
and he was dancing there.

00:06:10.014 --> 00:06:12.514
You wear a hat according to them it's Christian.

00:06:12.514 --> 00:06:17.047
You see, many Christians in India
believe that Christ was born in England.

00:06:20.517 --> 00:06:22.567
And that he was himself a Christian.

00:06:22.567 --> 00:06:23.677
He himself...  er?

00:06:23.677 --> 00:06:24.987
that he was a Christian.

00:06:25.027 --> 00:06:28.597
Yes. He Himself was a Christian
and was born in England.

00:06:28.637 --> 00:06:31.417
This they believe, actually
they believe in it.

00:06:31.443 --> 00:06:39.096
See there is a story, an interesting story of a villager who
was living… he used to come to Allahabad from his village.

00:06:39.101 --> 00:06:41.601
And he became a Christian.

00:06:41.621 --> 00:06:45.126
So he would always go to the river
Ganges, have a bath and go back.

00:06:45.158 --> 00:06:52.435
So the priest told them, “Now you can’t do, you
see, your religion has changed, you cannot do that.

00:06:52.473 --> 00:06:54.973
Now you have become a Christian.
You can’t go to the river.”

00:06:54.973 --> 00:06:59.450
River Ganges, the Christians
don’t go in India, do you know?

00:06:59.450 --> 00:07:01.680
They don’t go to the river Ganges.

00:07:01.680 --> 00:07:08.680
So, he said in his own language, “Sir, I have become
a ‘sahib’,” means, I have become an Englishman.

00:07:08.689 --> 00:07:11.189
“But I cannot give up my religion.”

00:07:11.189 --> 00:07:15.399
He thought he had become a sahib.

00:07:25.558 --> 00:07:30.223
And the names are also, they will
change it like this you see. Like a......

00:07:30.239 --> 00:07:35.553
like this gentleman’s name was Blondie. So ‘bhura’ (blond) means ‘bhura’.

00:07:35.553 --> 00:07:38.053
So he said, “Give me a good
name, like Alexander’s name.”

00:07:38.053 --> 00:07:42.694
So they called him
Alexander Bhura, you see.

00:07:42.715 --> 00:07:48.574
So his name was Alexander Bhura, so he thought
he had become a sahib you see, an Englishman.

00:07:48.594 --> 00:07:56.895
“And now they are asking me to give up my religion also, is
too much. I can’t give up my religion. I will go to Gangaji.”

00:07:58.435 --> 00:08:01.780
It’s very sad though, what
the missionaries did.

00:08:01.750 --> 00:08:15.104
I know in Hawaii and places like that, they destroyed what, from what I’ve read, appears to have been a very enlightened religion,

00:08:15.104 --> 00:08:20.669
which would have allowed, for
instance, Sahaja Yoga to just…

00:08:20.684 --> 00:08:22.689
they would have understood it instantly.

00:08:22.689 --> 00:08:25.189
And the Christians just chopped it off.

00:08:25.189 --> 00:08:33.912
In one generation. Of course the things that Cortez
did in Central America; terrible. Every.....

00:08:33.952 --> 00:08:34.893
Horrible things…

00:08:34.911 --> 00:08:41.803
Every book that had ever been… held any
knowledge that the Aztec came was destroyed.

00:08:41.824 --> 00:08:44.915
I mean, there is a history
behind the whole thing

00:08:44.934 --> 00:08:48.985
Thank God Columbus missed
his point, went to America.

00:08:48.988 --> 00:08:53.508
Otherwise, there would have
been no Sahaja Yoga here.

00:08:53.528 --> 00:08:58.070
There would be all Americans
roaming around in India, I think.

00:08:58.088 --> 00:09:09.565
With their AIDS, or with that kind of a trouble that
they have, because that would have been the thing.

00:09:16.635 --> 00:09:21.022
I think Hanumana must have done
that job, to take Columbus away.

00:09:21.019 --> 00:09:30.909
Because I can’t understand. This fellow, such
a clever man, went all the way from England.

00:09:30.940 --> 00:09:35.107
I mean from… Columbus was from Portuguese, was he?

00:09:35.141 --> 00:09:41.061
From Portugal, he went to a place –
Spanish, he was Spanish, I think: Spanish.

00:09:41.073 --> 00:09:46.683
He should have gone to India, I don’t
know how he reached America, you see.

00:09:46.711 --> 00:09:49.211
So must be Hanumana’s trick.

00:09:51.619 --> 00:09:53.313
That’s a long way.

00:09:53.329 --> 00:09:55.829
That’s what, he was there. But
they killed all the people.

00:09:57.064 --> 00:10:00.069
He did call that continent India.

00:10:00.069 --> 00:10:01.729
Yes they killed....

00:10:01.729 --> 00:10:02.829
That’s why we have the Red Indians.

00:10:02.829 --> 00:10:07.439
Yes. Red Indians. But the poor Red Indians
were killed and massacred completely.

00:10:07.439 --> 00:10:11.947
I mean the white people wherever they
went, they massacred all kinds.

00:10:11.977 --> 00:10:14.477
You see, the French, the
Portuguese… I tell you,

00:10:14.477 --> 00:10:17.217
the Portuguese now they look so horrid.

00:10:17.217 --> 00:10:24.107
But when they came to India – near Bombay,
you must have seen that Trimurti and all that.

00:10:24.102 --> 00:10:26.602
Did you go to see that Trimurti?

00:10:26.602 --> 00:10:30.173
That’s such a rock, black rock.

00:10:30.187 --> 00:10:35.858
And to hewn into it with this beauty
was really… must have been remarkable.

00:10:35.868 --> 00:10:38.908
But these people thought this rock
cannot be broken with anything,

00:10:38.908 --> 00:10:42.768
so they took cannons on
the ship and blasted it.

00:10:44.848 --> 00:10:50.671
That is such a strong rock that even now if you
have to nail them, you cannot put a drill on that.

00:10:50.692 --> 00:10:54.851
So, such a strong rock it is. And they
made such beautiful designs and things.

00:10:54.851 --> 00:11:00.340
But they blasted it. They were so much
against all these things, these Portuguese.

00:11:04.085 --> 00:11:07.035
So many temples, beautiful
temples they demolished.

00:11:07.035 --> 00:11:13.455
And the English also, terrible the English
were. English killed so many people in Calcutta.

00:11:13.455 --> 00:11:20.007
In a hole, they put them in a hole, known as
‘Hole of Calcutta’. And so many people were killed.

00:11:20.007 --> 00:11:20.705
Black hole of Calcutta.

00:11:20.705 --> 00:11:24.955
Black hole of Calcutta. And in Dhaka…

00:11:24.970 --> 00:11:26.460
Jallianwala Bagh,

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:30.180
Jallianwala Bagh, another thing.
Just killed people just like that.

